         I couldn't agree more with many of the posters here.  What were they thinking?!?!</P><P>You don't just overnight uberfy every caster in the game by bumping their spell lines and casting abilities through the roof while leaving every other advantage they already had to deal with their weakness in casting in tact. I love the lists that have been created here to show how these "poor, unfairly treated" NPC casters were hardly lacking in ANY other department.</P><P>Why should we have to bow to the arguement of "fair" anyways.  Where is that coming from.  Is it fair to the PC casters who have been awaiting balancing in this game for years to see the whole game thrown into the blender.  How "fair" is it that if you put a PC wiz up against an NPC wiz there is no way the PC would ever win due to (resistes, interupts, mana pools, hps, melee, casting ranges, etc etc.)  </P><P>I will accept these changes when PC caster are so uber that we can kill these NPC casters as quickly as they can kill us.  No.. nevermind.. I don't want to accept this mistake at all.  I don't agree with VI tactic of making such a mess of things that when they clean it up a little bit people thank them for it.  Remember the whole CH hate generation  change.  They threw it so far out of whack that when they came back a little everyone was saying thank you for it.  Same thing here.  Next week when they tone it down a bit everyone will be saying thanks and getting on with a life in game which will be even more out of balance than it was before the last patch.  Caster balancing will be even more broken.  Why?  Because now you will have to give even more healing to every priest class to handle AE and Rain damage, more resist buffs to handle the higher level spells, more stuns to help groups coup with casters, more damage to damage casters so they can kill these uber caster NPC mobs more quickly so melee doesn't die from all their uber spells. </P><P>In a sense they are going to have to go over THE WHOLE GAME again and rebalance everything.  Single group encounters in LGuk just became as touchy as old plane raids used to be.  Plane raids are more like high level mob encounters and so on so forth.</P><P>Soloing (except for fear kitting) just became nearly impossible when it comes to casting mobs.  Death and exp loss will be the near certain end to seeing a A_Casting_Mob_20levelsbelowyou_has landed a spell on you.  </P><P>VI, You broke the game, patch it back already.  And we can all have a good laugh about it.  Or leave it as is and add to your already full plate rebalancing the WHOLE GAME.  If you do leave it in you will begin to see many more people wanting Customer Service and many casual players leaving your game. </P><P>I loved the post on the casual two hour gamer.  You can't, post 50, recover the exp lost to an unrezzed death in 2 hours.  It would take multiple sessions to regain lost exp to that single death.  Well guess what, if you encounter a casting mob while solo you will be dieing more than you were before the patch.</P><P>I don't like be a hampster on the wheel for VI. I guess I am ok with having to "run on my wheel" to level up etc.  I have grown to like that.  But I don't like having my wheel spun upside down while I am on it.  Patch your patch and get this game back in line.</P><P>malachii</P><P>btw if I had recieved that kind of an answer from Alan I would be quite upset.  /rude</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Malachii on 06/07/2002  10:21:56<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
