         My only real problem with this change is the cast times npc's have. I was in Akheva soloing, and in the time it took me to cast FP, the transient patroller cast like 3 or 4 spells on me. I personally think it's great they use spells better, makes it more of a challenge. Lastly, the warlocks in ssra casting the 1100pt lifetaps should drop essence emeralds then :D</P><P>npc mana pool is really not that big. I DC an undead obulation in HS (wizzie npc) and after the first fight, he mostly just melee'd. (plus he had lower hps, and melee damage etc) It just appears that they have lots of mana, since you are chain fighting mobs that start FM.</P><P><BR>Effexor Darkmood<BR>60 Necro "Lich"<BR>Vis Maior<BR>Quellious<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
