        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This is by far the worst decision VI has done to this game.</P><P>This change will make playing in general much more dangerous.  Not that I'm bothered about that, I don't even mind that the mobs cast "Smarter".  But let's think about what that will mean:</P><P>Say for instance PoF raid.</P><P>Usually a Monk, SK, or Warrior pulling with sow.  Puller tags a mob and normally 3 or 4 buddies come with him.  Now he/she runs the mobs by the group for Tagging.  How is this suppose to work now?  What you will see happen is ALOT of CR of the puller.  Why, cause he/she is now rooted/mezzed/ST'd/Charmed? etc...</P><P>That's just one instance.  It will make raids to these places almost unbearable to endure.  Sure the PowerGaming type folks welcome this stuff, cause they are so bored with the same thing everyday.  </P><P>But I'm willing to bet that at least 50% of the player base hasn't done everything in every zone and is bored with the game the way it was pre-patch.  This just makes it more cumbersome and will eventually just flood the outdoor zones with people who can't stand to go into dungeons anymore, because they will be too hard.</P><P>An NPC that casts smarter isn't the real problem.  The spells available to the NPC's that has been changed is the issue.  Who wants a Glare lord (lvl 49 chanter w/pet) in fear AoE mezzing a raid party and wiping them out?  Makes no sense to me.</P><P></P><P><BR>Craigmandu<BR>55th Defiler<BR>On Tarrew Marr<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
